[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering JUnit dependencies**\n\nI'm thinking about the InjectedTestCase extending JUnit's TestCase. I wonder if generated tests need that specific class to compile, especially since the existing build doesn’t include JUnit 4. TCK has JUnit Jupiter, but does it cover everything? I need to check if javap needs classpath settings. If test imports InjectedTestCase, it looks like the JUnit dependency must be on the classpath. It raises questions about existing dependencies and setup for meaningful coverage. I'm evaluating whether the extra Maven dependency is necessary for the tests.\n\n**Examining dependency setups**\n\nIt seems like we don't need a deterministic setup for existing coverage. However, when looking into library usage, if the documentation says InjectedTest/InjectedTestCase work with JUnit, generated tests might require the junit:junit optional dependency to avoid failure. But meaningful coverage can actually be achieved without that old JUnit. I wonder if an extra dependency for javax.inject is necessary, possibly from sisu-guice. I'll need to verify that normal dependencies are resolved and consider running dependency resolution with `./gradlew dependencies`. Researching is key here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09de179fca31de8c016a3e60b12c048195bf7e64947c332602\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPmC6xrSM3yTCRvGeUkgekexOvXmrUW_Za6sUclcJsYv2hROTYb8mn5MDthQfpVdEYk_fzvPOZA-UQ5fFmXT6oWwLJlOyTCcrJzY3CFtF839RQXAUdUsuxTBdidomakP2D9iNw-H6N8ZIoV1omMDbepNo6pIjQa1AvrPsysit_t3sGHObknWHC3b5wher_bV_qVUIR71UBowUAZ6hMoRyLdFAuaAh4npdWEUPgAQduw_Mw-np9BIFTnNuklnaNCuaCa6bnCNjU0G2bvwsT0knnZL-UbUX-SsLMBNuvCiioFWEGp2T58JE9rBtG9U70gGRoeCvuJTPYyOyRBTRxC7tshWwASHmPl6X3dAlZPZkth5VvyKqoYH-bs-tYPOhcsfJu9GmyzFdtabpmOo-zfktIuxyi7bNdAKZM_8Nb47UkSaChiWcKPHlLRxrA-nwj1yAg09qhn1lI2J06N6xwsPHLJpjnem5Bcvc995SawguCCrnrYFWqjr8ypTrgNWepFSI