gpQmqG-nHqoe0YzdHObFmqx7IX_pa2oyIKhtg_N\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating TestNG with Gradle**\\n\\nI'm considering that the `testCompileClasspath` from Gradle isn't including TestNG, which might be causing issues. There's a possibility that existing test compilation didn't interact with `InjectedTest`. If generated tests reference `InjectedTest`, could there be a javac error related to `BeforeMethod` accessibility? I'm thinking about quickly testing this with a single file without modifying the repo—maybe in a temporary directory. Using the classpath resolved from Gradle along with the necessary jars seems challenging but might help clarify if TestNG is optional.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NNg2DPh8CwjO7SxxZfGMzrMd|fc_09de179fca31de8c016a3e60fe4e788195b384cfad60c6d6b4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY' > /tmp/sisu-cp.txt\nimport os, glob\nroot=os.path.expanduser('~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1')\ncoords=[\n('org.sonatype.sisu','sisu-inject-bean','2.4.1',''),\n('javax.enterprise','cdi-api','1.0',''),\n('javax.annotation','jsr250-api','1.0',''),\n('javax.inject','javax.inject','1',''),\n('org.sonatype.sisu','sisu-guice','3.1.5','no_aop'),\n('aopalliance','aopalliance','1.0',''),\n('com.google.guava','guava','11.0.2',''),\n('com.google.code.findbugs','jsr305','1.3.9',''),\n('org.eclipse.sisu','org.eclipse.sisu.inject','0.0.0.M4',''),\n('junit','junit','4.13.2',''),\n('org.hamcrest','hamcrest-core','1.3',''),\n]\npaths=[]\nfor g,a,v,cls in coords:\n    pattern=f'{root}/{g}/{a}/{v}/*/{a}-{v}' + (f'-{cls}' if cls else '') + '.jar'\n    ms=glob.glob(pattern)\n    if not ms: print('missing',pattern, file=os.sys.stderr)\n    paths += ms[:1]\nprint(':'.join(paths))\nPY\ncat > /tmp/TestInjected.java <<'EOF'\nimport org.sonatype.guice.bean.containers.InjectedTest;\npublic class TestInjected extends InjectedTest { }\nEOF\njavac -cp \"$(cat /tmp/sisu-cp.txt)\" /tmp/TestInjected.java 2>&1 | sed -n '1,